<p><b>British Columbia</b> (<span class="IPA nounderlines" style="white-space:nowrap;"><a href="/wiki/Media:En-ca-BritishColumbia.ogg" title="Media:En-ca-BritishColumbia.ogg"><img alt="En-ca-BritishColumbia.ogg" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Loudspeaker.svg/11px-Loudspeaker.svg.png" width="11" height="11" border="0" /></a> <a href="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/01/En-ca-BritishColumbia.ogg" class="internal" title="En-ca-BritishColumbia.ogg"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">ˌbrɪtɨʃ kəˈlʌmbiə</span></a> <small class="metadata">(<a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Media_help" title="Wikipedia:Media help">help</a>·<a href="/wiki/File:En-ca-BritishColumbia.ogg" title="File:En-ca-BritishColumbia.ogg">info</a>)</small></span>) (<b>BC</b>) (<a href="/wiki/French_language" title="French language">French</a>: <span lang="fr" xml:lang="fr"><i>la Colombie-Britannique</i></span>, <i>C.-B.</i>) is the westernmost of <a href="/wiki/Canada" title="Canada">Canada</a>'s <a href="/wiki/Provinces_and_territories_of_Canada" title="Provinces and territories of Canada">provinces</a> and is famed for its natural beauty, as reflected in its Latin motto, <i>Splendor sine occasu</i> ("Splendour without Diminishment"). It was the sixth province to join the <a href="/wiki/Canadian_Confederation" title="Canadian Confederation">Canadian Confederation</a>.</p>
<p>The capital of British Columbia is <a href="/wiki/Victoria,_British_Columbia" title="Victoria, British Columbia">Victoria</a>, the <a href="/wiki/List_of_the_100_largest_metropolitan_areas_in_Canada" title="List of the 100 largest metropolitan areas in Canada">15th largest metropolitan region</a> in Canada. The largest city is <a href="/wiki/Vancouver" title="Vancouver">Vancouver</a>, the third-largest <a href="/wiki/Metropolitan_area" title="Metropolitan area">metropolitan area</a> in Canada and the second-largest in the <a href="/wiki/Pacific_Northwest" title="Pacific Northwest">Pacific Northwest</a>.</p>
